SUMMARY:How to Work a Room and Land Your Dream Job
DESCRIPTION:Learn how to confidently meet diplomats and global profession
 als\, network effectively\, and get insider strategies for internships an
 d careers.Erin Huntington (https://hls.indiana.edu/about/deans-council/hu
 ntington-erin.html) built a career bridging government service and intern
 ational corporate strategy\, managing global teams and connecting policy\
 , advocacy\, and market access for one of the world's leading pharmaceuti
 cal companies.  Curious how to turn conferences\, networking\, and conver
 sations into real career opportunities? She'll share real-world strategie
 s that helped her move from Capitol Hill to global leadership—and how y
 ou can apply them too.What you'll get out of this session:      How to ap
 proach professionals\, start conversations\, and make connections that ma
 tter          Insider strategies for turning networking into internships\
 , mentors\, and career opportunities          Tools to tell your story co
 nfidently in interviews and professional settings          Tips for navig
 ating global conferences and international professional spaces      This 
 drop-in session is open to all HLS students. Light refreshments will be p
 rovided. Don't miss the chance to get concrete strategies that you can us
 e immediately at conferences\, internships\, and global career events!
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p data-start="227" data-end="496">  Learn h
 ow to confidently meet diplomats and global professionals\, network effec
 tively\, and get insider strategies for internships and careers.</p><p da
 ta-start="227" data-end="496"><img src="https://hls.indiana.edu/images/ab  out/deans-council/huntington-erin.jpg" alt="" loading="lazy"/></p><p data
 -start="498" data-end="842"><a href="https://hls.indiana.edu/about/deans-
 council/huntington-erin.html">Erin Huntington</a> built a career bridging
  government service and international corporate strategy\, managing globa
 l teams and connecting policy\, advocacy\, and market access for one of t
 he world's leading pharmaceutical companies.</p><p data-start="498" data-
 end="842">  Curious how to turn conferences\, networking\, and conversati
 ons into real career opportunities? She'll share real-world strategies th
 at helped her move from Capitol Hill to global leadership—and how you c
 an apply them too.</p><p data-start="844" data-end="886"><strong data-sta
 rt="844" data-end="884">What you'll get out of this session:</strong></p>
 <ul data-start="887" data-end="1235"><li data-start="887" data-end="975">
 <p data-start="889" data-end="975">      How to approach professionals\, 
 start conversations\, and make connections that matter    </p></li><li da
 ta-start="976" data-end="1073"><p data-start="978" data-end="1073">      
 Insider strategies for turning networking into internships\, mentors\, an
 d career opportunities    </p></li><li data-start="1074" data-end="1154">
 <p data-start="1076" data-end="1154">      Tools to tell your story confi
 dently in interviews and professional settings    </p></li><li data-start
 ="1155" data-end="1235"><p data-start="1157" data-end="1235">      Tips f
 or navigating global conferences and international professional spaces   
  </p></li></ul><p data-start="1237" data-end="1458">  This drop-in sessio
 n is open to all HLS students. Light refreshments will be provided. <stro
 ng>Don't miss the chance to get concrete strategies that you can use imme
 diately at conferences\, internships\, and global career events!</strong>
 </p>
